name: MajorInjuries
title: Major Injuries
description: This set of SNOMEDCT values contains major injury diagnoses, developed as a partner value set to be associated with a patient fall. These codes align with the ICD-10-CM codes that were identified as aligning with the NCC MERP Harm Taxonomy Codes E, F, G, H, I (used by the Pennsylvania Patient Safety Authority)  and the Abbreviated Injury Scale (AIS) with AIS score >2.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: The purpose of this SNOMED CT value set is to identify major injuries or death that could occur as a result of a fall within a hospital setting.),(Data Element Scope: This value set may use a model element related to Diagnosis.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes SNOMEDCT concepts that represent major injuries or death that could occur as a result of a fall within a hospital setting.),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes minor injuries and injuries as a result of a fall that could not occur within a hospital setting.)
